argin-bottom: .5em; float: right; padding: .5em 0 .8em 1.4em; background: none; width: auto;"> <div id="toc" class="toc"> <div class="toctitle"> <h2>Contents</h2> </div> <ul> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Kinds_of_asylum"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Kinds of asylum</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Art_and_entertainment"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Art and entertainment</span></a> <ul> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-3"><a href="#Companies"><span class="tocnumber">2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Companies</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-4"><a href="#Film"><span class="tocnumber">2.2</span> <span class="toctext">Film</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="#Literature"><span class="tocnumber">2.3</span> <span class="toctext">Literature</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-6"><a href="#Music"><span class="tocnumber">2.4</span> <span class="toctext">Music</span></a> <ul> <li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-7"><a href="#Albums"><span class="tocnumber">2.4.1</span> <span class="toctext">Albums</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-8"><a href="#Songs"><span class="tocnumber">2.4.2</span> <span class="toctext">Songs</span></a></li> </ul> </li> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-9"><a href="#Television"><span class="tocnumber">2.5</span> <span class="toctext">Television</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-10"><a href="#Video_games"><span class="tocnumber">2.6</span> <span class="toctext">Video games</span></a></li> </ul> </li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-11"><a href="#Places"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">Places</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-12"><a href="#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li> </ul> </div> </div> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Kinds_of_asylum">Kinds of asylum</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Asylum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Kinds of asylum">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(antiquity)" title="Asylum (antiquity)">Asylum (antiquity)</a>, places of refuge in ancient Greece and Rome <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Cities_of_Refuge" title="Cities of Refuge">Cities of Refuge</a>, places of refuge in ancient Judea</li> </ul> </li> <li><a href="/wiki/Benevolent_Asylum" title="Benevolent Asylum">Benevolent Asylum</a>, a 19th-century Australian institution for housing the destitute</li> <li>Church asylum or <a href="/wiki/Sanctuary" title="Sanctuary">sanctuary</a>, a right to be safe from arrest in the sanctuary of a church or temple</li> <li>Insane asylum or lunatic asylum, an obsolete type of institution for housing those deemed insane: see <a href="/wiki/Psychiatric_hospital" title="Psychiatric hospital">psychiatric hospital</a></li> <li>Orphan asylum or <a href="/wiki/Orphanage" title="Orphanage">orphanage</a>, an institution dedicated to caring for orphans</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Right_of_asylum" title="Right of asylum">Right of asylum</a> or political asylum</li> </ul> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Art_and_entertainment">Art and entertainment</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Asylum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Art and entertainment">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Companies">Companies</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Asylum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Companies">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <ul> <li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Asylum_Entertainment&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Asylum Entertainment (page does not exist)">Asylum Entertainment</a>, an American television production company</li> <li><a href="/wiki/The_Asylum" title="The Asylum">The Asylum</a>, an American film production company</li> </ul> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Film">Film</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Asylum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Film">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(1972_horror_film)" title="Asylum (1972 horror film)"><i>Asylum</i> (1972 horror film)</a>, a horror film starring Peter Cushing</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(1972_documentary_film)" title="Asylum (1972 documentary film)"><i>Asylum</i> (1972 documentary film)</a>, a film featuring the psychiatrist R. D. Laing</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(1997_film)" title="Asylum (1997 film)"><i>Asylum</i> (1997 film)</a>, an American film starring Robert Patrick and Malcolm McDowell</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(2003_film)" title="Asylum (2003 film)"><i>Asylum</i> (2003 film)</a>, an American short documentary</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(2005_film)" title="Asylum (2005 film)"><i>Asylum</i> (2005 film)</a>, a British drama by David Mackenzie based on the novel by Patrick McGrath (see below)</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(2008_film)" title="Asylum (2008 film)"><i>Asylum</i> (2008 film)</a>, an American horror film by David R. Ellis</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(2014_film)" title="Asylum (2014 film)"><i>Asylum</i> (2014 film)</a>, an American horror film</li> </ul> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Literature">Literature</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Asylum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Literature">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(comics)" title="Asylum (comics)">Asylum (comics)</a>, two characters in the Marvel Comics universe</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(Maximum)" class="mw-redirect" title="Asylum (Maximum)"><i>Asylum</i> (Maximum)</a>, a comic series</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(Darvill-Evans_novel)" title="Asylum (Darvill-Evans novel)"><i>Asylum</i> (Darvill-Evans novel)</a>, a 2001 <i>Doctor Who</i> novel</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(McGrath_novel)" title="Asylum (McGrath novel)"><i>Asylum</i> (McGrath novel)</a>, a 1996 novel by Patrick McGrath</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylums_(book)" title="Asylums (book)"><i>Asylums</i> (book)</a>, a 1961 nonfiction book by Erving Goffman</li> <li><i>Asylum</i>, a comic published by <a href="/wiki/New_Comics_Group" title="New Comics Group">New Comics Group</a></li> <li><i>The Asylum; or Alonzo and Melissa</i>, a 1811 American novel by <a href="/wiki/Isaac_Mitchell" title="Isaac Mitchell">Isaac Mitchell</a></li> <li><i>The Asylum: The Renegades Who Hijacked the World's Oil Market</i>, a 2011 book by <a href="/wiki/Leah_McGrath_Goodman" title="Leah McGrath Goodman">Leah McGrath Goodman</a></li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(magazine)" title="Asylum (magazine)">Asylum (magazine)</a>, a magazine about mental health and psychiatry</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_(series)" title="Asylum (series)"><i>Asylum</i> (series)</a>, a young adult horror series</li> </ul> <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Music">Music</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Asylum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Music">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Asylum_Records" title="Asylum Records">Asylum Records</a>, an American record label</li> </ul> <h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Albums">Albums</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Asylum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Albums">edit</a><span class=